
1) What is a Java package?
Packages are groups of related classes.

2) What is the CLASSPATH variable all about?
CLASSPATH is a parameter that specifies the location of user-defined classes and packages

3) What does the package structure mirror?
A file folder.

4 How do packages affect access to Java classes?
By setting visibility through public private protected and default.

5) What is an interface?
An interface is like an abstract class where you can specify one or more methods that have no body.

6) What makes interfaces unique?
A class that includes the interface needs to fully implement the methods defined by that interface or declare as abstract.

7) What keyword is used to specify that a class is going to use a separate interface?
implements

8) What makes interfaces so useful?
It allows multiple inheritance.

9) What was added in JDK 8 that makes interfaces even more useful?
You can now add a default implementation.

10) How many interfaces can a single class implement?
Unlimited